<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="<%= locale %>">

<head>
  <%- include('partials/meta') %>
    <title>Server Time Comparison Guide | Complete NTP Sync Tutorial · SyncTime</title>
    <meta name="description"
      content="Master server time synchronization with our complete guide. Learn NTP setup, ticketing timing strategies, and millisecond-level accuracy techniques." />
    <meta name="keywords" content="server time guide, NTP synchronization, ticketing tips, time sync tutorial" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="<%= domain %>/<%= locale %>/guide" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1" />
    <meta property="og:type" content="article" />
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="SyncTime - Server Time Comparison Service" />
    <meta property="og:title" content="Server Time Comparison Guide | Complete NTP Sync Tutorial" />
    <meta property="og:description"
      content="Master server time synchronization with NTP setup, ticketing timing strategies, and millisecond-level accuracy techniques for success." />
    <meta property="og:url" content="<%= domain %>/<%= locale %>/guide" />
    <meta property="og:image" content="<%= domain %>/og-image.png" />
    <meta property="og:image:width" content="1200" />
    <meta property="og:image:height" content="630" />
    <meta property="og:image:type" content="image/png" />
    <meta property="og:locale" content="<%= locale === 'ko' ? 'ko_KR' : locale === 'jp' ? 'ja_JP' : locale === 'zh-tw' ? 'zh_TW' : 'en_US' %>" />
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image" />
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Server Time Comparison Guide | Complete NTP Sync Tutorial" />
    <meta name="twitter:description"
      content="Learn NTP setup, ticketing timing strategies, and millisecond-level accuracy techniques with our complete guide." />
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="<%= domain %>/og-image.png" />

    <script type="application/ld+json">
      {
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "How do I use the server time comparison service?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "Simply enter the target website's URL in the main page input field and click the 'Check Time' button to see an approximate current time based on the server. No login or additional information is required."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "Why is NTP more accurate?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "NTP (Network Time Protocol) synchronizes device time with millisecond-level accuracy by comparing and correcting multiple layers of standard time. In situations where timing precision is critical, such as ticketing, synchronizing your device with NTP in advance is the safest approach."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "What does this service provide?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "We check the time in the header response from your entered URL and display it as a reference. Due to network path and server environment characteristics, there may be errors of tens to hundreds of milliseconds, so please use it as a reference alongside NTP-based device time."
            }
          },
          {
            "@type": "Question",
            "name": "When will more accurate features be available?",
            "acceptedAnswer": {
              "@type": "Answer",
              "text": "In future versions, we plan to provide reference time synchronized with our own NTP server, making it easy to check high-precision time on various devices. We will notify you when the update is complete."
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    </script>
</head>

<body>
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="content-page">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span>Guide</span>
      </nav>

      <section>
        <h2>1. How do I use it?</h2>
        <p>
          Simply enter the target website's URL in the main page input field and click <strong>Check Time</strong> to
          see
          an approximate current time based on the server. No login or additional information is required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2. Why is NTP more accurate?</h2>
        <p>
          NTP (Network Time Protocol) synchronizes device time with millisecond-level accuracy by comparing and
          correcting
          multiple layers of standard time. In situations where timing precision is critical, such as ticketing,
          synchronizing your device with NTP in advance is the safest approach.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3. What does this service provide?</h2>
        <p>
          We check the time in the header response from your entered URL and display it <strong>as a reference</strong>.
          Due to network path and server environment characteristics, there may be errors of tens to hundreds of
          milliseconds, so please use it as a reference alongside NTP-based device time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4. When will more accurate features be available?</h2>
        <p>
          In future versions, we plan to provide reference time synchronized with our own NTP server, making it easy to
          check high-precision time on various devices. We will notify you when the update is complete.
        </p>
      </section>

      <hr style="margin: 2rem 0; border: none; border-top: 1px solid #ddd;" />

      <nav class="internal-links" style="margin-top: 2rem;">
        <h3>Related Pages</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/">Back to Main</a></li>
          <li><a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>


</body>

</html>